{{TWCleanup2}} 
[[File:Leaf morphology acuminate.png|Acuminate shape of leaf ]]
Tapering to a long point, such as in the [[Leaf shape|shape of leaves]] or other botanical features such as the [[stamen]] filaments.

==Etymology==
From the 16th century Latin acuminatus 'pointed', from acuminare 'sharpen to a point', and acuere 'sharpen'.<ref>https://en.oxforddictionaries.com/definition/acuminate</ref>

