The '''United Nations Asian and Pacific Training Centre for Information and Communication Technology for Development '''(UN-APCICT) aims to improve, for the region of Asia and Pacific, Information and Communication Technology (ICT) knowledge for long-term economic growth and sustainable development of the region. Opened in 2006<ref name ="G/29/2006"/> and located in Songdo Techno Park in [[Incheon]], [[South Korea|Republic of Korea]], the Centre is Asia's first training centre for Information Communication Technology for Development. UN-APCICT is established by the [[United Nations Economic and Social Commission for Asia and the Pacific]] (UNESCAP).<ref name="关于仁川 新闻杂志">{{Cite web|url = http://chinese.incheon.go.kr/posts/814/4703?rnum=7&curPage=2|title = 诚招参加UN APCICT研讨会的大学生|publisher = 仁川广域市}}</ref><ref name ="G/29/2006">{{cite web|url=http://www.unapcict.org/news/opening|author=United Nations Information Services|date=2006-06-16|title=Asia's First Training Centre for Information Communication Technology for Development Opens in the Republic Of Korea}}</ref>

